title: Fidelium (FID) Achieves Market Capitalization of $9.56 Million
content: Filed Under: Cryptocurrencies - Investing   Fidelium (CURRENCY:FID) traded down 5.2% against the US dollar during the 1-day period ending at 17:00 PM Eastern on June 2nd. One Fidelium token can now be bought for $0.0861 or 0.00001129 BTC on popular exchanges. During the last week, Fidelium has traded 37.8% lower against the US dollar. Fidelium has a total market capitalization of $9.56 million and $337,178.00 worth of Fidelium was traded on exchanges in the last day.   Here is how other cryptocurrencies have performed during the last day:   Get Fidelium alerts:   Ripple (XRP) traded up 4.4% against the dollar and now trades at $0.64 or 0.00008417 BTC.   Stellar (XLM) traded 3.9% higher against the dollar and now trades at $0.30 or 0.00003901 BTC.   IOTA (MIOTA) traded 1% higher against the dollar and now trades at $1.88 or 0.00024687 BTC.   TRON (TRX) traded 5.5% higher against the dollar and now trades at $0.0609 or 0.00000799 BTC.   NEO (NEO) traded up 3.9% against the dollar and now trades at $56.55 or 0.00741909 BTC.   Tether (USDT) traded 0.9% lower against the dollar and now trades at $0.99 or 0.00012998 BTC.   VeChain (VEN) traded 10% higher against the dollar and now trades at $3.72 or 0.00048808 BTC.   Binance Coin (BNB) traded 4.8% higher against the dollar and now trades at $14.68 or 0.00192586 BTC.   Ontology (ONT) traded 9.2% higher against the dollar and now trades at $7.67 or 0.00100615 BTC.   Zilliqa (ZIL) traded 7.2% higher against the dollar and now trades at $0.12 or 0.00001546 BTC.
